						<summary>

						<p>On the same slab [No. 134] left side.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Tribhuvanamalla [Vikramāditya VI] 1106 A.D.</hi> </p>						

						<p>It records a grant of land to Hollimayya and Mallayya at Baḷḷaniṭṭage by Chandaladēvi, the queen of Vikramāditya VI. It refers to the measuring rod <hi rend="italic">piriyakōlu.</hi></p>						

						<p>It is dated in Chālukya Vikrama year 30, Vyaya Pushya ba. 13, Tuesday, <hi rend="italic">uttarāyaṇasankrānti</hi> corresponding to 1106 A.D., December 25, Tuesday, f.d.t. 05.</p>						

						</summary>
